class="https://lccn.loc.gov/no96038967 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2010112931 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2012000503 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2007003439"><summary>Miscellaneous collection of Islamic sectarian polemical works. Volume not dated. Distinct scribal nastaʿlīq by the same hand throughout. Annotations in margins. Stamped foliation. Lacking original binding. Binding damaged (combed marble paper with brown leather edging over pasteboards), labels. Folios mostly bound; cropped, wormholes, later repairs. Condition poor. IOL microfilm, IOL NEG 681.</summary><textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang><msItem n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_323-item1"><locus from="1v" to="11v">ff. 1v-11v</locus><textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang><note><p>Delhi Persian 323(a), ff. 1v-11v.</p><p>Transcript of a letter on criticisms to the three Shīʿah sectarian treatises, 
                <title key="work_23073">Ṣavārim</title>, 
                <title key="work_23073">Ḥusām</title>, and 
                <title key="work_23073">Z̲ū al-Fiqār</title>, from 
                <persName key="person_f8130" role="aut">Javād ʿAlī</persName>addressed to his spiritual leader and the author, 
                <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164657192.0x000001 viaf_36805746" role="rcp">Mawlavī Dildār ʿAlī</persName>(d. 1235/1819).
                        </p><p>Not dated at end.</p></note><author /><title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_23073">Naql-i khaṭṭ</title><title xml:lang="fa" key="work_23073">نقل خطّ</title></msItem><msItem n="2" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_323-item2"><locus from="12r" to="15r">ff. 12r-15r</locus><note><p>Delhi Persian 323(b), ff. 12r-15r.</p><p>Brief sectarian polemical treatise on doubts and concerns over the treatise entitled 
                <title key="work_23074">al-Ṣavārim</title>, by an unnamed author.
                        </p><p>Not dated at end.</p></note><textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang><title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_23074">al-Shubhāt ʿalá al-Ṣavārim</title><title xml:lang="fa" key="work_23074">الشّبهات على الصّوارم</title></msItem><msItem n="3" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_323-item3"><locus from="16r" to="18r">ff. 16r-18r</locus><note><p>Delhi Persian 323(c), ff. 12r-15r.</p><p>Brief sectarian polemical treatise critiquing Shīʿī accounts of the 
                <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656957.0x000001 viaf_27868234" role="subject">Caliph ʿUmar</persName>striking the stomach of 
                <persName key="viaf_30328354" role="subject">Fāṭimah bint Muḥammad</persName>, as related in the treatise entitled 
                <title key="work_23075">Z̲ū al-Fiqār</title>, by an unnamed author.
                        </p><p>Not dated at end.</p></note><textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang><title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_23075">al-Shubhāt ʿalá Z̲ū al-Fiqār</title><title xml:lang="fa" key="work_23075">الشّبهات على ذو الفقار</title></msItem><msItem n="4" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_323-item4"><locus from="18r" to="21r">ff. 18r-21r</locus><note><p>Delhi Persian 323(d), ff. 18r-21r.</p><p>Transcript of a theological letter from 
                <persName key="viaf_36805746" role="aut">Mawlavī Dildār ʿAlī</persName>sent to one of his followers on points of detail in the writings of 
                <persName key="viaf_53999017" role="rcp">Shāh ʿAbd al-ʿAzīz Dihlavī</persName>the muḥaddis̲.
                        </p><p>Not dated at end.</p></note><textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang><title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_23073">Naql-i khaṭṭ</title><title xml:lang="fa" key="work_23073">نقل خطّ</title><author><persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_36805746">Mawlavī Dildār ʿAlī</persName></author></msItem><msItem n="5" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_323-item5"><locus from="21v" to="28r">ff. 21v-28r</locus><note><p>Delhi Persian 323(e), ff. 21v-28r .</p><p>Transcript of theological doubts and concerns relating to a letter from 
                <persName key="viaf_36805746" role="ant">Mawlavī Dildār ʿAlī</persName>.
                        </p><p>Not dated at end.</p><p>Annotations.</p></note><textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang><title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_23076">Naql-i shubhāt-i mushakkak</title><title xml:lang="fa" key="work_23076">نقل شبهات مشكّك</title></msItem><msItem n="6" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_323-item6"><locus from="29r" to="30r">ff. 29r-30r</locus><note><p>Delhi Persian 323(f.), ff. 29r-30r.</p><p>Transcript of a letter on Islamic sectarian polemics in 
                <persName key="person_f8131" role="oth">Lucknow</persName>and 
                <placeName>Delhi</placeName>from 
                <persName key="viaf_36805746" role="aut">Mawlavī Dildār ʿAlī</persName>addressed to 
                <persName key="person_f7698" role="rcp">Mawlavī ʿAbd al-Qādir Khān ṣāḥib</persName>.
                        </p><p>Not dated at end.</p></note><textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang><title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_23077">Khaṭṭ</title><title xml:lang="fa" key="work_23077">خطّ</title><author><persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_36805746">Mawlavī Dildār ʿAlī</persName></author></msItem><msItem n="7" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_323-item7"><locus from="30v" to="31r">ff. 30v-31r</locus><note><p>Delhi Persian 323(g), ff. 30v-31r.</p><p>Transcript of a brief reply to a letter on theological questions addressed to 
                <persName key="person_f7392" role="rcp">Mawlānā Muḥammad Rashīd al-Dīn Khān ṣāḥib</persName>.
                        </p><p>Not dated at end.</p></note><textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang><title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_23078">Javāb-i khaṭṭ</title><title xml:lang="fa" key="work_23078">جواب خطّ</title></msItem><msItem n="8" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_323-item8"><locus from="32r" to="52v">ff. 32r-52v</locus><note><p>Delhi Persian 323(h), ff. 32r-52v.</p><p>Transcript of a rebuttal to the first of several theological postulations set out in the book written and sent by 
                <persName key="person_f8132" role="ant">Khān ṣāḥib</persName>.
                        </p><p>Not dated at end.</p></note><textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang><title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_23079">Javāb-i ʿaqīdah-'i avval</title><title xml:lang="fa" key="work_23079">جواب عقيدهٴ اوّل</title></msItem><msItem n="9" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_323-item9"><locus from="53r" to="96v">ff. 53r-96v</locus><note><p>Delhi Persian 323(i), ff. 53r-96v.</p><p>Untitled theological treatise by 
                <persName key="person_f7392" role="aut">Mawlānā Muḥammad Rashīd al-Dīn Khān</persName>written in rebuttal to a treatise by 
                <persName key="person_f8133" role="ant">Muḥammad Qulī, Muftī of Meerath</persName>, written circa 1231/1816.
                        </p><p>The work begins with a lengthy Arabic preface.</p><p>Not dated at end.</p></note><textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang><note /><author><persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7392">Mawlānā Muḥammad Rashīd al-Dīn Khān</persName></author></msItem><msItem n="10" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_323-item10"><locus from="97r" to="102v">ff. 97r-102v</locus><note><p>Delhi Persian 323(j), ff. 97r-102v.  </p><p>Theological treatise answering jibes on the permissibility of music and song stated in the 
                <title key="work_23081">Tuḥfah-'i Is̲nāʾ ʿAsharīyah</title>of 
                <persName key="viaf_53999017" role="ant">ʿAbd al-ʿAzīz ibn Aḥmad Dihlavī</persName>(d. 1239/1823-4).
                        </p><p>Not dated at end.</p></note><textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang><title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_23081">Suʾāl</title><title xml:lang="fa" key="work_23081">سوٴال</title></msItem><msItem n="11" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_323-item11"><locus from="102v" to="106v">ff. 102v-106v</locus><note><p>Delhi Persian 323(k), ff. 102v-106v.  </p><p>Untitled polemic treatise comparing Sunnī and Shīʿah perceptions of divinity by an unnamed author.</p><p>Not dated at end.</p></note><textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang><author /></msItem><msItem n="12" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_323-item12"><locus from="106v" to="107v">ff. 106v-107v</locus><note><p>Delhi Persian 323(l), ff. 106v-107v.  </p><p>Untitled polemic treatise on the subject of the murder of the 
                <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164657175.0x000001 viaf_34436377" role="subject">Imam and Caliph ʿAlī</persName>(d. 40/661) by an unnamed author.
                        </p><p>Not dated at end.</p></note><textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang><note /></msItem><msItem n="13" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_323-item13"><locus from="107v" to="114v">ff. 107v-114v</locus><author /><note><p>Delhi Persian 323(m), ff. 107v-114v.  </p><p>Untitled polemic treatise on questions over the role of 
                <persName key="person_f7201" role="subject">Jibrāʾīl</persName>in the revelation of the 
                <title key="work_23084">Qurʾān</title>to the 
                <persName key="viaf_97245226" role="subject">Prophet Muḥammad</persName>, by an unnamed author.
                        </p><p>Not dated at end.</p></note><textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang><note /></msItem><msItem n="14" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_323-item14"><locus from="114v" to="117v">ff. 114v-117v</locus><author /><note><p>Delhi Persian 323(n), ff. 114v-117v.  </p><p>Untitled theological treatise by an unnamed author.</p><p>Not dated at end.</p></note><textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang><note /></msItem><msItem n="15" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_323-item15"><locus from="117v" to="119v">ff. 117v-119v</locus><author /><note><p>Delhi Persian 323(o), ff. 117v-119v.  </p><p>Untitled theological treatise on a point of detail raised by 
                <persName key="viaf_90051632" role="ant">Shaykh Jalāl al-Dīn Suyūṭī</persName>by an unnamed author.
                        </p><p>Not dated at end.</p></note><textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang><note /></msItem><msItem n="16" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_323-item16"><locus from="120r" to="127r">ff. 120r-127r</locus><author><persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f8133">Mawlavī Muḥammad Qulī</persName><persName xml:lang="fa" key="person_f8133">مولوى محمّد قلى</persName></author><title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_23087">Risālah-'i taṭhīr al-muʾminīn ʿan al-najāsat al-mushrikīn</title><title xml:lang="fa" key="work_23087">رسالهٴ تطهير الموٴمنين عن النّجاست المشركين</title><note><p>Delhi Persian 323(p), ff. 120r-127r.  </p><p>Theological treatise by 
                <persName key="person_f8133" role="aut">Mawlavī Muḥammad Qulī, Muftī of Meerath</persName>, writing in favour of Sunnī opinions, despite professing the Shīʿah Imāmī faith.
                        </p><p>Not dated at end.</p></note><textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang><note /></msItem><msItem n="17" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_323-item17"><locus from="128r" to="128r">f. 128r</locus><author /><note><p>Delhi Persian 323(q), f. 128r.  </p><p>Brief statement on proofs for the Shīʿah faith, by an unnamed author.</p><p>Not dated at end.</p></note><textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang><note /></msItem><msItem n="18" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_323-item18"><locus from="128v" to="133r">ff. 128v-133r</locus><author /><title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_23089">Javāb-i khaṭṭ</title><title xml:lang="fa" key="work_23089">جواب خطّ</title><note><p>Delhi Persian 323(r), ff. 128v-133r.  </p><p>Fragment of a theological treatise by 
                <persName key="person_f8130" role="aut">Javād ʿAlī</persName>addressed to his spiritual leader and the author on many Shīʿī treatises, 
                <persName key="viaf_36805746" role="rcp">Mawlavī Dildār ʿAlī</persName>(d. 1235/1819).
                        </p><p>The descriptive title has been corrected and re-transcribed vertically in the margin by the main scribe.</p><p>This copy ends abruptly without formal conclusion.</p><p>Not dated at end.</p></note><textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang><note /></msItem></msContents><physDesc><objectDesc form="codex"><supportDesc material="chart"><extent>133 ff. 
